Articles about TAIPEI







Renovation style – Five hotels for your next trip to Taipei

                    From gourmet delights to lively night markets and historic architecture, there’s a lot just waiting to be discovered in Taipei. To kickstart your journey to Taiwan’s capital, HereNow introduces five charming hotels that have been established in renovated buildings.                   

                    Text: Tatsuko Morita                  

POSTED on 13.09.2016


Tweet


 




PAGE 1 of 3


1
2
3


 




The Door Inn
Simple and stylish in Dadaocheng



“I want people to use this hotel as a starting point for discovering Taipei”, says the owner of The Door Inn in Dadaocheng.

Dadaocheng was the most prosperous area in Taipei during the 19th and 20th centuries. Since that time, many of the buildings have been retained as important cultural assets and now attract both domestic and international travellers to the area.



The area has seen a recent influx of shops brimming with originality, which has created an interesting mix of new and old. 


The Door Inn has been designed with a minimal aesthetic. In order to make the most of its surroundings, the hotel’s interior spaces have been completed in a simple and stylish manner. 



The old four-storey building features rooms with subtle white tones that create a sense of comfort. This considered approach extends to the large windows that provide views of the surrounding area and bring a sense of Taipei’s old charms into the hotel interior. 



The guest rooms are located on the second, third and fourth floors, while the communal space on the ground floor includes a kitchen and dining space where guests can interact with one another.


Guests can often be found chatting, sharing dinner or celebrating with a party in the communal space. Accordingly to the owner, nothing gives him more joy than seeing relationships build between those who meet at the hotel.


The Door Inn
Address: No. 23, Anxi St, Datong District, Taipei City
Phone Number：02-2557-7045
Price：NT$ 1500-4000
URL：https://www.facebook.com/thedoorinn/


